The climate mitigation (adaptation) plan is a mobilization and action plan based on structuring principles. Thus, the actions proposed in the plan are that it:
-must allow sustainable, balanced and resilient development of territories, from a social, economic and environmental point of view;  “no regrets”;
-they will bring benefits regardless of the magnitude of future climate change;
-must avoid any risk of maladaptation, that is to say actions which, in the long term, would ultimately prove to be irrelevant, even counterproductive or harmful; 
-help improve the robustness and resilience of aquatic environments.

